        <h1>What is Cloud Computing?</h1>
        <p>Cloud computing is the on-demand delivery of IT resources over the internet with pay-as-you-go pricing.</p>

        <h2>Three Main Service Models</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>IaaS</strong> — Infrastructure as a Service (e.g., AWS EC2)</li>
            <li><strong>PaaS</strong> — Platform as a Service (e.g., AWS Elastic Beanstalk)</li>
            <li><strong>SaaS</strong> — Software as a Service (e.g., Google Drive)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>✅ No need to manage physical servers</li>
            <li>✅ Automatically scale up and down</li>
            <li>✅ Pay only for what you use</li>
            <li>✅ Global reach in minutes</li>
        </ul>
